abstract: Wells Fargo said its earnings in the third quarter rose 7 percent, after a good showing by its retail franchise and the Wachovia Corporation branches it acquired.

lead_paragraph: Within weeks of scooping up the failed banking operations of Washington Mutual in late 2008, JPMorgan Chase began phasing out the WaMu brand, replacing signs on retail branches. WaMu accounts became Chase accounts. Just over a year later, the conversion was done, turning the WaMu name into a relic of the financial crisis, Eric Dash reports in The New York Times.
